{
  "name": "Angel — DA Fault Healer",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Angel Fault Healer\n\nRuns only when the Referee reports `angel_enabled` (false during the **baseline** ablation arm, so the harness can measure kubelet + Argo without the Angel). Polls each tenant's `/db-ping` and acts only where it is actually needed:\n\n- **Can't reach the app** (connection error — e.g. a crash) → stand down. That's the kubelet's lane (liveness restart).\n- **DB:Unreachable** (mini-db scaled to 0 / bad image) → stand down. Manifest drift Argo selfHeal owns.\n- **DB:CorruptedTable:ZeroNotes** (truncate — green-but-dead, no drift, not restart-healable) → **POST /admin/restore** (restore from backup). Verify → `agent-action`. If restore fails / no backup → `escalated` (unrecoverable).\n\nThe Angel only acts on what neither the kubelet nor Argo can see. The Referee attributes each round's resolving layer by ablation, not by this label.\n\n**To arm:** the Referee sets angel_enabled via /start-match (arm=agent).",
        "height": 260,
        "width": 1144,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        32,
        -304
      ],
      "id": "setup-notes",
      "name": "Setup Notes"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "seconds",
              "secondsInterval": 15
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [
        0,
        0
      ],
      "id": "schedule",
      "name": "Poll Every 15s"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "url": "http://referee.da-referee.svc.cluster.local/is-active",
        "options": {
